1
00:00:03,378 --> 00:00:05,797
[theme song playing]

2
00:01:22,624 --> 00:01:25,419
[Light] The human whose name
is written in this notebook...

3
00:01:25,877 --> 00:01:26,795
shall die…

4
00:01:27,546 --> 00:01:29,673
-[Takuo laughs] Woo!
-[Lady] Help me!

5
00:01:29,756 --> 00:01:31,091
[Light] Now… what will happen?

6
00:01:31,216 --> 00:01:32,426
TAKUO SHIBUIMARU
ACCIDENTAL DEATH

7
00:01:35,512 --> 00:01:36,763
The Death Note...

8
00:01:37,014 --> 00:01:37,931
It's for real!

9
00:01:39,683 --> 00:01:40,934
[screams]

10
00:01:43,645 --> 00:01:45,814
Any human who's used a Death Note

11
00:01:46,023 --> 00:01:49,026
can neither go to heaven nor hell
for eternity.

12
00:01:49,943 --> 00:01:53,030
[Light] I want the world to know
of my existence.

13
00:01:53,238 --> 00:01:56,722
That there's someone passing
righteous judgement on the wicked!

14
00:01:58,092 --> 00:01:59,051
And I…

15
00:01:59,578 --> 00:02:01,371
I will become the God of this New World!

16
00:02:01,496 --> 00:02:04,416
CONFRONTATION

17
00:02:04,833 --> 00:02:07,711
[teacher] He found himself overwhelmed
with happiness and satisfaction...

18
00:02:08,211 --> 00:02:10,297
[girl] I have no idea what he was thinking
coming to my house,

19
00:02:10,380 --> 00:02:11,673
but I am so through with him.

20
00:02:11,840 --> 00:02:14,426
[boy] Seriously? So, what happened
with your dad after that?

21
00:02:14,509 --> 00:02:15,427
[teacher] Alright then.

22
00:02:15,510 --> 00:02:16,428
-Yagami?
-Huh?

23
00:02:16,511 --> 00:02:18,513
Please recite this line for us.

24
00:02:18,680 --> 00:02:19,890
[Light] Sure.

25
00:02:22,259 --> 00:02:25,137
"Having finally made his dream a reality,
he was overwhelmed.

26
00:02:25,812 --> 00:02:27,731
Both by the magnitude of his achievement,

27
00:02:27,814 --> 00:02:30,776
and by the joy and happiness
that it brought him."

28
00:02:31,443 --> 00:02:32,778
That was very well done,

29
00:02:32,903 --> 00:02:34,529
but I'm not surprised, of course.

30
00:02:34,655 --> 00:02:37,074
Absolutely flawless. Very good.

31
00:02:40,243 --> 00:02:43,121
Well then,
we'll leave it at that for today.

32
00:02:43,497 --> 00:02:45,040
-[chairs scraping]
-[footsteps receding]

33
00:02:45,248 --> 00:02:46,875
[bell ringing]

34
00:02:48,627 --> 00:02:50,962
-[students chatter]
-[Ryuk] I thought it'd never end.

35
00:02:51,046 --> 00:02:53,632
How do you do this every day?
It's so boring here.

36
00:02:53,757 --> 00:02:55,425
Hey, where're you going?

37
00:02:55,509 --> 00:02:57,511
Hey, Light! Are you listening to me?

38
00:02:57,803 --> 00:02:58,804
[quietly] Don't talk to me.

39
00:02:59,596 --> 00:03:02,766
Unlike you, people can still hear me
when I talk out loud.

40
00:03:03,183 --> 00:03:04,810
Heh, well aren't you boring.

41
00:03:05,310 --> 00:03:06,311
Hey, what's up, Light?

42
00:03:06,436 --> 00:03:09,147
-We were just going to head down to the--
-Sorry, I'm a little busy today.

43
00:03:10,691 --> 00:03:12,526
You don't have anything to do.

44
00:03:12,651 --> 00:03:15,362
Aren't you just going to go home
and hang out in your room, as usual?

45
00:03:15,946 --> 00:03:18,031
What are you talking about?
Of course, I have something to do.

46
00:03:18,907 --> 00:03:21,618
Yes, something very important.

47
00:03:23,453 --> 00:03:27,457
[news reporter] There was more violence
across the city today. Another stabbing.

48
00:03:27,624 --> 00:03:32,129
This time at a restaurant in the heart
of the Kabuki-cho district of Shinjuku.

49
00:03:32,254 --> 00:03:33,296
[chomping]

50
00:03:33,422 --> 00:03:35,132
Mm. Hey, Light.

51
00:03:35,215 --> 00:03:37,509
[swallows] I'm talking to you.

52
00:03:37,634 --> 00:03:38,719
[Light] What is it?

53
00:03:39,594 --> 00:03:41,596
[Ryuk] Why are you working so hard?

54
00:03:41,930 --> 00:03:43,682
[Light] I can't afford to waste any time.

55
00:03:44,725 --> 00:03:47,352
I have a very small window
to write names in this notebook.

56
00:03:48,103 --> 00:03:50,564
I only have from when I get
home from school until I go to bed.

57
00:03:50,831 --> 00:03:52,522
I still need to sleep,
so I can maintain my average

58
00:03:54,778 --> 00:03:56,987
Obviously, I can't be sleeping in class.

59
00:03:57,154 --> 00:03:59,906
Plus, there's all the studying at home
and at cram school.

60
00:04:00,040 --> 00:04:01,748
I can't let myself get too tired.

61
00:04:02,198 --> 00:04:04,667
It will start to affect my health
and my mental performance.

62
00:04:04,995 --> 00:04:07,712
If I'm serious
about trying to create an ideal world

63
00:04:07,789 --> 00:04:08,999
that's free from evil

64
00:04:09,082 --> 00:04:11,001
then I need to make the most of my time.

65
00:04:13,051 --> 00:04:14,379
[Sayu] Huh? Weird.

66
00:04:14,463 --> 00:04:17,007
Hey, Light, what's going on?
Why is your door locked?

67
00:04:17,549 --> 00:04:19,634
[Light] It's Sayu.
What is it?

68
00:04:19,718 --> 00:04:21,428
[Sayu] Can you help me with my homework?

69
00:04:22,220 --> 00:04:23,764
Uh, yeah. Okay.

70
00:04:27,142 --> 00:04:29,060
We're doing quadratic equations in math.

71
00:04:29,770 --> 00:04:32,314
Sorry to interrupt.
I know you're studying right now,

72
00:04:32,397 --> 00:04:35,066
but I'm like the only person in my class
who doesn't get this stuff.

73
00:04:35,567 --> 00:04:36,693
Thanks so much!

74
00:04:36,777 --> 00:04:37,736
No problem.

75
00:04:37,986 --> 00:04:40,030
I'd be careful if I were you.

76
00:04:40,447 --> 00:04:44,201
If anyone else touches that notebook
you've got hidden in the drawer right now,

77
00:04:44,326 --> 00:04:46,036
they'll be able to see me too.

78
00:04:46,203 --> 00:04:47,078
Huh?

79
00:04:47,204 --> 00:04:49,581
He waits till now to mention
that important detail?

80
00:04:49,831 --> 00:04:51,082
Damn Shinigami.

81
00:04:51,792 --> 00:04:53,710
What's wrong? Are you alright?

82
00:04:53,835 --> 00:04:55,003
[Light] Hm? It's nothing.

83
00:04:55,212 --> 00:04:57,130
So, what exactly don't you understand?

84
00:04:57,437 --> 00:04:58,465
What are you stuck on?

85
00:04:58,590 --> 00:05:00,133
[Sayu] Um… well…

86
00:05:00,258 --> 00:05:01,593
I think all of it.

87
00:05:02,469 --> 00:05:04,471
[delegate 1] There have been 52 deaths
that we're aware of,

88
00:05:04,596 --> 00:05:06,295
and that's just in the past week.

89
00:05:06,389 --> 00:05:08,433
[delegate 2] Every single one of them
involved a heart attack.

90
00:05:08,806 --> 00:05:11,394
[delegate 1] They were all criminals
who were either being held in prison

91
00:05:11,520 --> 00:05:13,563
or who were wanted by police
for outstanding crimes.

92
00:05:14,105 --> 00:05:15,982
And I think it's safe to say
there are other criminals

93
00:05:16,107 --> 00:05:17,567
whose deaths are unaccounted for.

94
00:05:18,151 --> 00:05:21,152
In which case the death toll
could be well over 100.

95
00:05:23,740 --> 00:05:27,118
Uh… morning, Chief.
They started the meeting without you.

96
00:05:27,285 --> 00:05:30,038
That's fine. I had to take an urgent call
from headquarters.

97
00:05:30,619 --> 00:05:32,415
At any rate, these were criminals

98
00:05:32,499 --> 00:05:35,224
who were probably
facing execution sooner or later.

99
00:05:35,299 --> 00:05:36,834
Perhaps we shouldn't be--

100
00:05:36,934 --> 00:05:39,172
Why should it matter
if it's a criminal or someone innocent?

101
00:05:39,256 --> 00:05:41,689
Last time I checked,
murder was still murder!

102
00:05:41,800 --> 00:05:44,052
It's still too early
to consider these a homicide.

103
00:05:44,469 --> 00:05:47,639
Then how did all these people have
heart attacks at the exact same time?

104
00:05:47,806 --> 00:05:49,455
That's not coincidence, it's murder!

105
00:05:49,605 --> 00:05:51,142
You think it's possible

106
00:05:51,226 --> 00:05:54,435
to simultaneously kill all these people
in different locations?

107
00:05:54,510 --> 00:05:56,189
We're treating this as
an elaborate murder plot

108
00:05:56,273 --> 00:05:58,149
that's been carried out by
a large organization.

109
00:05:58,615 --> 00:06:00,416
If it is a large organization,

110
00:06:00,491 --> 00:06:04,197
I'm sure I'm not alone
in suspecting the FBI or CIA.

111
00:06:04,739 --> 00:06:06,116
[delegate] I dare you to say that again!

112
00:06:06,199 --> 00:06:08,994
Now, now, this is not the time
to be joking around!

113
00:06:09,286 --> 00:06:13,164
We need to confirm that these
are indeed homicides and not coincidences!

114
00:06:13,373 --> 00:06:15,166
How? Autopsy results show

115
00:06:15,250 --> 00:06:18,169
that in all of these cases, the victims
died of a sudden heart attack.

116
00:06:18,378 --> 00:06:20,964
Investigating a series of heart attacks
is pointless.

117
00:06:21,089 --> 00:06:22,674
I don't see what else we can learn.

118
00:06:22,883 --> 00:06:23,884
Absolutely.

119
00:06:23,967 --> 00:06:27,429
If these people had been shot or stabbed,
at least we'd have something to go on.

120
00:06:27,971 --> 00:06:31,850
If that's the case, it looks as if
we'll have no choice but to bring in L.

121
00:06:34,853 --> 00:06:36,187
[delegates muttering]

122
00:06:38,356 --> 00:06:41,026
Uh, Chief. What's this "L"
they're talking about?

123
00:06:41,192 --> 00:06:44,112
Right, I forgot that it's your first time
at this conference.

124
00:06:44,577 --> 00:06:46,954
We don't know L's real name
or whereabouts.

125
00:06:47,079 --> 00:06:48,992
In fact, we still don't even know
what he looks like.

126
00:06:49,910 --> 00:06:53,788
However, he's managed to solve every case
he's ever taken on.

127
00:06:53,955 --> 00:06:56,833
And he's tackled some of the greatest
mysteries this world has ever known.

128
00:06:56,917 --> 00:07:00,142
He hides in the shadows,
but he's the best of the best.

129
00:07:00,242 --> 00:07:02,505
A last resort. Our trump card.

130
00:07:02,964 --> 00:07:05,759
[delegate] But I've heard this "L"
is extremely arrogant

131
00:07:05,842 --> 00:07:08,918
I understand he'll only take on cases
that he's personally interested in.

132
00:07:09,043 --> 00:07:10,013
That's exactly right!

133
00:07:10,096 --> 00:07:12,724
Besides, we don't even know
how to contact him!

134
00:07:13,183 --> 00:07:15,850
[Watari] L is already on the move.

135
00:07:27,113 --> 00:07:31,284
[Watari] Gentlemen, L has already begun
his investigation into these incidents.

136
00:07:31,368 --> 00:07:32,410
[delegate] Watari?

137
00:07:32,744 --> 00:07:34,162
Huh? Who's that?

138
00:07:34,412 --> 00:07:37,207
That man's the only known person
who can contact L.

139
00:07:37,380 --> 00:07:40,251
Nobody knows his true identity either.

140
00:07:40,933 --> 00:07:42,295
-[murmuring]
-[Watari] Please be silent.

141
00:07:42,585 --> 00:07:44,923
L would now like to address the delegates.

142
00:07:49,166 --> 00:07:52,138
[L, voice altered via voice distorter]
Greetings to all of you at the ICPO.

143
00:07:53,306 --> 00:07:55,097
I am L.

144
00:07:56,226 --> 00:07:57,727
[Ryuk] What are we doing here anyway?

145
00:07:57,894 --> 00:08:01,022
I don't understand why we're
sneaking around this dump. Tell me.

146
00:08:01,487 --> 00:08:04,567
Isn't it obvious? You told me that anyone
who touches the Death Note

147
00:08:04,651 --> 00:08:06,027
will be able to see you.

148
00:08:06,152 --> 00:08:09,280
I can't afford to carry something
this dangerous with me anymore.

149
00:08:10,031 --> 00:08:10,907
Up until now,

150
00:08:11,032 --> 00:08:13,118
I thought that if my family
ever saw the notebook,

151
00:08:13,493 --> 00:08:16,371
I can tell them I was keeping records
of various criminals

152
00:08:16,454 --> 00:08:19,249
in preparation
for becoming a detective one day.

153
00:08:19,405 --> 00:08:22,085
But I'm walking a very fine line
right now.

154
00:08:22,627 --> 00:08:24,170
I don't want to think about it,

155
00:08:24,254 --> 00:08:26,089
but if I make one mistake,

156
00:08:26,339 --> 00:08:28,049
I might end up killing my own family.

157
00:08:35,849 --> 00:08:39,208
[L] The difficulty of this case lies
on its unprecedented scope.

158
00:08:39,308 --> 00:08:40,770
And make no mistake.

159
00:08:40,854 --> 00:08:42,897
We are witnessing an atrocious act
of mass murder,

160
00:08:42,981 --> 00:08:44,998
one that is unforgivable.

161
00:08:45,167 --> 00:08:49,093
This case cannot be solved
without the full cooperation of the ICPO.

162
00:08:49,218 --> 00:08:52,947
That is all of the police organizations
you represent throughout the world.

163
00:08:53,047 --> 00:08:57,829
You need to make the decision to fully
support the investigation at this meeting.

164
00:08:57,910 --> 00:08:58,794
Also...

165
00:08:58,873 --> 00:09:02,126
I require additional cooperation
from Japan's National Police Agency.

166
00:09:03,293 --> 00:09:04,169
Huh?

167
00:09:04,294 --> 00:09:06,568
What? Why Japan in particular?

168
00:09:06,713 --> 00:09:09,674
[L] Whether the guilty party
is an individual or a group,

169
00:09:09,758 --> 00:09:12,177
there's a strong possibility
that they are Japanese.

170
00:09:13,011 --> 00:09:15,930
And even if they are not,
we can be sure they're hiding in Japan.

171
00:09:16,097 --> 00:09:17,682
What is all this based on?

172
00:09:18,433 --> 00:09:20,310
[L] Why Japan, you ask?

173
00:09:20,377 --> 00:09:22,671
I think I will be able to provide you
with proof of that

174
00:09:22,813 --> 00:09:24,856
after I directly confront the culprit.

175
00:09:25,899 --> 00:09:27,317
A direct confrontation?

176
00:09:27,701 --> 00:09:32,203
[L] At any rate, I would like to set up
the investigation headquarters in Japan.

177
00:09:33,323 --> 00:09:34,532
Hmm...

178
00:09:37,199 --> 00:09:39,037
That was easier to make
than I thought it'd be.

179
00:09:39,329 --> 00:09:40,246
Huh?

180
00:09:40,413 --> 00:09:42,207
Does that mean
you were able to hide the notebook?

181
00:09:42,749 --> 00:09:45,460
Yeah. I hid it right here in this drawer.

182
00:09:45,994 --> 00:09:48,204
But it doesn't seem to be
particularly well hidden.

183
00:09:49,172 --> 00:09:50,882
You left the key in the lock.

184
00:09:51,132 --> 00:09:52,550
[Light] And that's the whole point.

185
00:09:53,176 --> 00:09:54,135
I intentionally left the key

186
00:09:54,260 --> 00:09:56,638
in the most noticeable place
I could think of.

187
00:09:59,349 --> 00:10:01,101
Isn't that just a regular diary?

188
00:10:01,392 --> 00:10:02,477
[Light] That's what it is.

189
00:10:02,560 --> 00:10:05,605
I'm guessing that once most people
find the diary inside my desk,

190
00:10:05,931 --> 00:10:08,099
that'll probably satisfy their curiosity.

191
00:10:08,650 --> 00:10:10,735
But... the real key...

192
00:10:11,194 --> 00:10:12,112
is this.

193
00:10:12,571 --> 00:10:15,246
Just an everyday item you'd expect
to find lying around on my desk.

194
00:10:15,983 --> 00:10:17,373
A regular ball-point pen,

195
00:10:17,673 --> 00:10:19,341
and all I need is this part.

196
00:10:19,744 --> 00:10:21,121
[Ryuk] So that's the key?

197
00:10:21,704 --> 00:10:23,331
Yeah. If you look closely,

198
00:10:23,732 --> 00:10:26,067
you'll find that there's a small hole
underneath the drawer.

199
00:10:27,127 --> 00:10:29,045
Then you just insert this...

200
00:10:33,633 --> 00:10:35,760
[Ryuk] Aha. A fake bottom.

201
00:10:36,169 --> 00:10:40,054
The diary will distract most people,
so I doubt anyone will find it.

202
00:10:40,154 --> 00:10:42,183
-[Light] But that's not all.
-Oh?

203
00:10:42,592 --> 00:10:45,009
Even if someone figures out
that there's a fake base,

204
00:10:45,109 --> 00:10:47,102
I've set things up
so that there's no way they could

205
00:10:47,177 --> 00:10:48,754
get their hands on the notebook.

206
00:10:50,233 --> 00:10:51,276
You see,

207
00:10:51,693 --> 00:10:54,112
once the ink reservoir is inserted,
it acts as an insulator,

208
00:10:54,279 --> 00:10:56,739
preventing the flow of electricity
around this circuit.

209
00:10:57,574 --> 00:10:59,534
When the fake base of the drawer's
put back,

210
00:10:59,659 --> 00:11:02,579
this piece of rubber
also prevents the flow of electricity.

211
00:11:02,829 --> 00:11:04,873
However, if someone were to try

212
00:11:04,998 --> 00:11:06,624
and force the bottom of the drawer open,

213
00:11:07,041 --> 00:11:08,042
the circuit would connect

214
00:11:08,168 --> 00:11:11,087
and now would ignite the gasoline
contained in this thin plastic casing,

215
00:11:12,630 --> 00:11:14,507
instantly setting the notebook on fire.

216
00:11:15,164 --> 00:11:16,457
The way I’ve got it set up,

217
00:11:16,682 --> 00:11:18,742
all the evidence
would be completely destroyed.

218
00:11:19,702 --> 00:11:20,652
If I'm ever questioned,

219
00:11:20,702 --> 00:11:22,396
I'll just say
that I was hiding the real diary

220
00:11:22,484 --> 00:11:24,513
because I didn't want anyone to see it.

221
00:11:24,634 --> 00:11:26,365
It sounds like a pretty believable excuse.

222
00:11:26,561 --> 00:11:28,938
I mean... it is my diary after all.

223
00:11:30,148 --> 00:11:32,775
I've heard of humans finding Death Notes
in the past

224
00:11:32,859 --> 00:11:34,611
and typically,
the biggest problem they had

225
00:11:34,777 --> 00:11:36,446
is finding a good place to hide it.

226
00:11:36,779 --> 00:11:40,825
But you, Light, you're probably the first
to have given it this much thought.

227
00:11:41,450 --> 00:11:43,702
Though, it's a pretty risky setup
from the look of it.

228
00:11:44,662 --> 00:11:46,539
If you make even the slightest mistake,

229
00:11:46,623 --> 00:11:48,458
you could be badly burned.

230
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:50,001
Risky?

231
00:11:50,126 --> 00:11:51,961
You say
the strangest thing sometimes, Ryuk.

232
00:11:52,962 --> 00:11:55,506
This whole thing has been a risk
since the very beginning,

233
00:11:55,591 --> 00:11:57,551
from the moment I obtained the Death Note.

234
00:11:59,010 --> 00:12:00,637
I'm sorry, but compared to that,

235
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:02,722
this doesn't even qualify as a risk to me.

236
00:12:03,139 --> 00:12:05,475
In fact, it actually protects me.

237
00:12:06,226 --> 00:12:09,148
It all comes down to a choice:
would I prefer to be executed

238
00:12:09,228 --> 00:12:10,813
or deal with a little house fire?

239
00:12:30,875 --> 00:12:32,850
[announcer] Last night
in the West Tokyo penitentiary,

240
00:12:32,960 --> 00:12:36,745
Naoki Koro Kitayama, originally sentenced
to 15 years for armed robbery,

241
00:12:36,870 --> 00:12:40,468
was reported to have died
of a sudden heart attack at the age of 32.

242
00:12:40,644 --> 00:12:43,085
This is just the most recent death
in a steadily growing number

243
00:12:43,185 --> 00:12:45,014
of cases involving inmates
dying of heart attacks.

244
00:12:45,139 --> 00:12:47,850
[student 1] This is unbelievable.
Criminals are dropping like flies lately.

245
00:12:48,184 --> 00:12:50,826
[student 2] It's a little scary,
but at the same time, it's kinda cool.

246
00:12:50,876 --> 00:12:52,853
[student 1] Just make sure
you don't do anything bad.

247
00:12:52,953 --> 00:12:55,149
[student 3] I wouldn't be surprised
if the police were behind this.

248
00:12:55,275 --> 00:12:57,816
[student 2] No way.
The police don't have that kind of power.

249
00:12:57,891 --> 00:12:59,904
-Don't you know about him?
-[student 3] Hmm? About who?

250
00:13:00,488 --> 00:13:02,437
[student 1] Kira. You know, Kira.

251
00:13:02,699 --> 00:13:04,701
[student 4] I wonder
who's gonna be killed next.

252
00:13:04,826 --> 00:13:07,829
KIRA, KILL EVERYONE

253
00:13:07,912 --> 00:13:08,913
SEND MESSAGE?
SEND

254
00:13:09,049 --> 00:13:09,927
[computer chimes]

255
00:13:09,998 --> 00:13:11,416
NAME: ROCOCO
KIRA, KILL EVERYONE - NAME: MISERY

256
00:13:11,541 --> 00:13:13,126
-[Light] Ryuk, you should check this out.
-[Ryuk] Huh?

257
00:13:13,668 --> 00:13:16,546
Websites like this
are popping up everywhere lately.

258
00:13:17,812 --> 00:13:19,937
[Ryuk] "The Legend of Kira the Savior."

259
00:13:20,049 --> 00:13:21,592
Huh. Sounds pretty cool.

260
00:13:21,801 --> 00:13:22,969
Is this about you?

261
00:13:23,136 --> 00:13:25,138
Yeah. I think
they've taken the name "Kira"

262
00:13:25,221 --> 00:13:26,848
from the English word "killer."

263
00:13:27,015 --> 00:13:29,198
Can't say I'm too happy about that, but...

264
00:13:29,434 --> 00:13:31,978
it looks like that's the name
they've decided to give me.

265
00:13:32,201 --> 00:13:35,621
When I search the word Kira, I'm pulling
up tons of sites just like this one.

266
00:13:35,981 --> 00:13:37,506
The media hasn't picked up on it.

267
00:13:37,824 --> 00:13:39,816
They're still calling this
"a succession of unexplained deaths

268
00:13:40,236 --> 00:13:42,503
among the world's
most hardened criminals."

269
00:13:42,848 --> 00:13:43,754
But…

270
00:13:43,829 --> 00:13:46,990
the people of the world can already sense
that there's something happening.

271
00:13:47,252 --> 00:13:50,269
They know there's someone out there
passing righteous judgment.

272
00:13:50,913 --> 00:13:51,998
Oh?

273
00:13:52,790 --> 00:13:54,715
[Light] Human beings are like that, Ryuk.

274
00:13:55,418 --> 00:13:56,294
Huh.

275
00:13:56,502 --> 00:13:58,963
Although this would probably
never happen in school,

276
00:13:59,036 --> 00:14:01,090
let's say that students
were asked to discuss

277
00:14:01,196 --> 00:14:03,176
whether bad people deserve to die.

278
00:14:03,676 --> 00:14:06,777
Well, you can bet that everyone would
give the politically correct answer.

279
00:14:07,388 --> 00:14:09,182
It's just wrong to kill people.

280
00:14:09,557 --> 00:14:10,975
[Light] That's what they're bound to say.

281
00:14:11,517 --> 00:14:13,978
Of course, that's the correct response
to give, right?

282
00:14:14,479 --> 00:14:16,779
Humans will always try
to maintain appearances

283
00:14:16,854 --> 00:14:19,108
when they're in public.
That's just how we are.

284
00:14:19,506 --> 00:14:21,194
But this is how they really feel.

285
00:14:21,475 --> 00:14:22,985
Most are too afraid to support me

286
00:14:23,060 --> 00:14:24,947
as they’re worried about
what others will think.

287
00:14:25,270 --> 00:14:27,264
Many would rather deny my existence.

288
00:14:27,489 --> 00:14:30,042
But on the Internet,
where you can remain anonymous,

289
00:14:30,142 --> 00:14:31,746
support for Kira is growing.

290
00:14:32,419 --> 00:14:34,504
Maybe people are afraid
to say it out loud,

291
00:14:34,604 --> 00:14:36,084
but they all understand what's happening.

292
00:14:36,501 --> 00:14:39,087
Someone's making the bad guys
disappear one by one.

293
00:14:39,420 --> 00:14:42,379
Those who have done no wrong
are cheering for Kira in their hearts

294
00:14:42,454 --> 00:14:44,384
because they have nothing to fear,

295
00:14:44,456 --> 00:14:46,552
while those who have done wrong
are on the run.

296
00:14:46,719 --> 00:14:49,180
They're forced to hide
from an unknown enemy.

297
00:14:49,711 --> 00:14:51,288
This is how it should be.

298
00:14:51,641 --> 00:14:52,725
It's perfect.

299
00:14:52,809 --> 00:14:54,900
Everything is going just like I planned.

300
00:14:55,103 --> 00:14:56,813
THE PROGRAM IS INTERRUPTED
FOR A SPECIAL BROADCAST

301
00:14:57,355 --> 00:14:59,399
We'd like to apologize
for the interruption.

302
00:14:59,482 --> 00:15:01,192
As of now we're bringing you

303
00:15:01,317 --> 00:15:04,320
a live worldwide broadcast
from Interpol's ICPO.

304
00:15:04,487 --> 00:15:06,364
Hm? What's this?

305
00:15:06,656 --> 00:15:07,698
Interpol?

306
00:15:07,805 --> 00:15:10,123
[announcer]
We now take you live to the ICPO.

307
00:15:10,758 --> 00:15:12,829
I head up
an International Police Task Force

308
00:15:12,912 --> 00:15:14,662
which includes all member nations.

309
00:15:15,112 --> 00:15:16,582
I am Lind L. Tailor,

310
00:15:17,541 --> 00:15:19,966
otherwise known as L.

311
00:15:20,293 --> 00:15:22,969
What? Who is this guy?

312
00:15:23,172 --> 00:15:24,549
[Soichiro] So this is how it all begins.

313
00:15:25,049 --> 00:15:26,218
[Matsuda] But, sir, I don't get it.

314
00:15:26,318 --> 00:15:28,136
He's never actually
shown his face before, right?

315
00:15:28,344 --> 00:15:29,971
Why would he choose to do it now?

316
00:15:30,430 --> 00:15:32,515
-It must mean L's serious about this.
-Hm.

317
00:15:33,057 --> 00:15:36,042
L, we've followed every single one
of your orders.

318
00:15:36,393 --> 00:15:40,606
Now, it's time for you to prove
what you said to the ICPO.

319
00:15:41,338 --> 00:15:44,527
Criminals around the world
are being murdered by a serial killer.

320
00:15:44,708 --> 00:15:48,095
I consider this crime to be the most
atrocious act of murder in history.

321
00:15:48,270 --> 00:15:49,313
I will not rest

322
00:15:49,388 --> 00:15:52,599
until the person or persons responsible
are brought to justice.

323
00:15:52,699 --> 00:15:55,494
Kira, I will hunt you down.
I will find you.

324
00:15:55,569 --> 00:15:57,707
He seems certain he'll catch you.

325
00:15:58,113 --> 00:15:59,459
Hm. That fool.

326
00:15:59,625 --> 00:16:01,085
He'll never find me.

327
00:16:01,752 --> 00:16:03,296
He'll have to get this first.

328
00:16:03,785 --> 00:16:05,256
And as long as the police don't find it,

329
00:16:05,339 --> 00:16:07,467
there won't be any evidence
to convict me,

330
00:16:07,898 --> 00:16:10,659
which means that catching me
will be absolutely impossible.

331
00:16:10,880 --> 00:16:11,934
[sighs]

332
00:16:12,096 --> 00:16:14,604
I anticipated that the police
would get involved

333
00:16:14,679 --> 00:16:16,309
and that something like this might happen.

334
00:16:16,765 --> 00:16:20,594
Kira, I've got a pretty good idea
what your motivation might be,

335
00:16:20,694 --> 00:16:22,773
and I can guess what you hope to achieve.

336
00:16:23,080 --> 00:16:27,236
However,
what you're doing right now is evil.

337
00:16:28,827 --> 00:16:31,032
You think… I'm evil?

338
00:16:33,057 --> 00:16:34,368
I am justice!

339
00:16:34,499 --> 00:16:36,977
I protect the innocent
and those who fear evil!

340
00:16:37,077 --> 00:16:40,839
I'm the one who will become the god
of a new world that everyone desires!

341
00:16:40,914 --> 00:16:45,135
All those who would oppose that god,
they are the ones who are truly evil!

342
00:16:46,214 --> 00:16:48,090
I guess you're just too stupid, L.

343
00:16:48,456 --> 00:16:49,331
Well, too bad.

344
00:16:49,406 --> 00:16:52,826
This could've been a lot more interesting
if you'd only been a bit smarter.

345
00:16:53,554 --> 00:16:56,641
[pen scratching]

346
00:16:58,111 --> 00:16:59,940
[chuckles]

347
00:17:04,899 --> 00:17:06,442
[Light laughs]

348
00:17:07,716 --> 00:17:10,635
I'll show the world what happens
when you cross me.

349
00:17:11,280 --> 00:17:14,075
The entire world is watching… L.

350
00:17:18,913 --> 00:17:20,122
Five more seconds.

351
00:17:20,456 --> 00:17:21,332
Four.

352
00:17:21,457 --> 00:17:22,375
Three.

353
00:17:22,500 --> 00:17:23,376
Two.

354
00:17:23,709 --> 00:17:24,627
One.

355
00:17:25,753 --> 00:17:27,463
[groans]

356
00:17:33,511 --> 00:17:36,556
[laughs maniacally]

357
00:17:36,937 --> 00:17:39,141
What's wrong?
You got nothing else to say?

358
00:17:44,605 --> 00:17:47,108
[L] [through distorter]
[gasps] I had to test this, just in case,

359
00:17:47,233 --> 00:17:50,111
but I-- I never thought
it would actually happen.

360
00:17:51,070 --> 00:17:52,280
Kira…

361
00:17:52,488 --> 00:17:55,533
it seems you can kill people
without having to be there in person.

362
00:17:56,792 --> 00:17:59,392
I wouldn't have believed it
if I hadn't just witnessed it.

363
00:18:00,788 --> 00:18:02,415
Listen to me, Kira.

364
00:18:03,255 --> 00:18:05,465
If you did, indeed, kill Lind L. Tailor,

365
00:18:05,540 --> 00:18:07,692
the man who you just saw
die on television,

366
00:18:07,795 --> 00:18:11,972
I should tell you that he was an inmate
whose execution was scheduled for today.

367
00:18:12,247 --> 00:18:13,347
That was not me.

368
00:18:13,426 --> 00:18:14,385
[Light] What?

369
00:18:14,510 --> 00:18:16,429
[L] The police arrested him
in absolute secrecy,

370
00:18:16,918 --> 00:18:20,141
so you wouldn't have heard about him
on TV or through the internet.

371
00:18:20,347 --> 00:18:21,934
It appears that not even you

372
00:18:22,059 --> 00:18:24,734
have access to information
about these types of criminals.

373
00:18:25,730 --> 00:18:26,897
[cackles]

374
00:18:27,064 --> 00:18:28,232
He got you there.

375
00:18:28,765 --> 00:18:33,176
[L] But I assure you, L is real.
I do exist.

376
00:18:33,276 --> 00:18:34,176
Now…

377
00:18:34,376 --> 00:18:35,862
try to kill me!

378
00:18:36,115 --> 00:18:38,140
[Light] You… you bastard.

379
00:18:38,240 --> 00:18:39,815
-[L] What's wrong? Hurry up.
-[man 1] What the hell is going on?

380
00:18:39,915 --> 00:18:41,773
-[L] Come on, right now. Kill me!
-[man 1] He's really taking this too far.

381
00:18:41,873 --> 00:18:43,645
[man 2] Are you trying
to kill yourself, L?

382
00:18:43,745 --> 00:18:45,012
-[bystander 1] What's going on?
-[bystander 2] Look,

383
00:18:45,062 --> 00:18:46,423
-it's Kira versus L!
-[L] Come on. What are you waiting for?

384
00:18:46,498 --> 00:18:48,030
[bystander 3]
A live broadcast of a killing?

385
00:18:48,174 --> 00:18:49,591
[L] You better do it.
Come on, Kira, kill me.

386
00:18:49,666 --> 00:18:51,470
-[bystander 4] Amazing!
-[bystander 5] Do it, Kira!

387
00:18:51,595 --> 00:18:53,989
-[bystander 6] Someone, stop this!
-[L] What's the matter? Can't you do it?

388
00:18:54,227 --> 00:18:55,556
[Light exhales shakily]

389
00:18:58,596 --> 00:19:01,547
[L] Well Kira, it seems that you
can't kill me after all.

390
00:19:02,058 --> 00:19:03,267
[cackles]

391
00:19:03,684 --> 00:19:05,770
[in normal voice]
So, there are some people you can't kill.

392
00:19:06,604 --> 00:19:08,272
You've given me a useful hint.

393
00:19:08,773 --> 00:19:10,149
[distorted] Let me return the favor.

394
00:19:10,531 --> 00:19:13,069
I'll tell you something
that I think you'll find interesting.

395
00:19:13,417 --> 00:19:15,780
Although this was announced
as a worldwide broadcast,

396
00:19:15,988 --> 00:19:17,114
the truth is,

397
00:19:17,370 --> 00:19:20,966
we are only broadcasting
in the Kanto region of Japan.

398
00:19:21,041 --> 00:19:21,911
[Light gasps]

399
00:19:21,991 --> 00:19:26,046
I had planned to broadcast this message
around the world until we found you,

400
00:19:26,387 --> 00:19:27,998
but it looks like that won't be necessary.

401
00:19:28,248 --> 00:19:29,835
I now know where you are.

402
00:19:29,919 --> 00:19:30,836
[cackles]

403
00:19:30,961 --> 00:19:32,919
This L guy is pretty good.

404
00:19:33,297 --> 00:19:36,342
[L] The police treated your first killing
as an unrelated incident,

405
00:19:36,425 --> 00:19:37,385
but in actuality,

406
00:19:37,510 --> 00:19:40,096
the first of your victims
was a suspect in Sinjuku.

407
00:19:41,178 --> 00:19:43,766
Of all the criminals that have recently
died of heart attacks,

408
00:19:43,849 --> 00:19:46,477
this one's crime was, by far,
the least serious.

409
00:19:46,977 --> 00:19:50,523
Furthermore, his crime was
only ever reported inside Japan.

410
00:19:50,962 --> 00:19:53,401
[in normal voice] I used that information
to deduce this much.

411
00:19:54,110 --> 00:19:55,277
[distorted] You are in Japan

412
00:19:55,403 --> 00:19:58,489
and your first victim was little more
than an experiment,

413
00:19:58,614 --> 00:20:01,325
which means you haven't been killing
for very long.

414
00:20:02,034 --> 00:20:03,077
[Light gasps]

415
00:20:03,933 --> 00:20:06,253
[L] We decided to broadcast in Kanto first

416
00:20:06,428 --> 00:20:07,915
because of its large population,

417
00:20:08,040 --> 00:20:09,500
and, luckily, we found you.

418
00:20:10,418 --> 00:20:12,169
To be completely honest with you,

419
00:20:12,336 --> 00:20:14,755
I never expected that things
would go this well…

420
00:20:14,820 --> 00:20:16,689
but it won't be too long now

421
00:20:16,764 --> 00:20:19,215
before I'll be able to sentence you
to death.

422
00:20:19,808 --> 00:20:22,888
L has…
certainly lived up to his reputation.

423
00:20:22,972 --> 00:20:25,975
Mhmm. He proved that Kira exists,

424
00:20:26,100 --> 00:20:29,186
that the deaths were murders,
and that he is here in Japan.

425
00:20:29,854 --> 00:20:31,856
Naturally, I am very interested to know

426
00:20:31,981 --> 00:20:34,907
how you're able to commit these murders
without being present…

427
00:20:35,207 --> 00:20:37,542
but I don't mind waiting
a little bit longer.

428
00:20:37,592 --> 00:20:39,068
[in normal voice]
You can answer all of my questions

429
00:20:39,143 --> 00:20:40,294
when I catch you…

430
00:20:41,054 --> 00:20:43,423
[distorted] Let's meet again soon, Kira.

431
00:20:44,671 --> 00:20:45,849
[Light exhales]

432
00:20:53,711 --> 00:20:54,795
Really?

433
00:20:56,422 --> 00:20:58,765
He's gonna sentence me to death?

434
00:20:59,790 --> 00:21:01,761
Sounds interesting.

435
00:21:01,927 --> 00:21:03,652
I accept your challenge, L.

436
00:21:04,711 --> 00:21:09,018
Each of them has to hunt down the other
without knowing the other's name or face.

437
00:21:09,143 --> 00:21:12,396
And the first one
whose identity is revealed will die.

438
00:21:12,772 --> 00:21:14,396
Humans are...

439
00:21:14,521 --> 00:21:16,298
so much fun.

440
00:21:16,400 --> 00:21:17,359
L...

441
00:21:17,777 --> 00:21:18,778
Kira...

442
00:21:19,153 --> 00:21:21,197
[L and Kira] I will hunt you down
wherever you're hiding

443
00:21:21,322 --> 00:21:22,281
and I will eliminate you!

444
00:21:22,656 --> 00:21:24,283
-I am...
-I am...

445
00:21:25,159 --> 00:21:26,285
[L and Kira] ... justice!

446
00:21:26,368 --> 00:21:32,374
TO BE CONTINUED

447
00:21:37,838 --> 00:21:42,760
[theme song playing]
